By Udora Orizu in Abuja The Speaker of the House of Representatives, Hon. Femi Gbajabiamila, has advised the Nigerian youth to be productive and self-reliant at this time. Gbajabiamila, in a statement issued by his Special Adviser, Media and Publicity, Lanre Lasisi, in commemoration of Nigeria’s maiden youth day, said the youth have a lot of potentials in them, which they must work assiduously towards achieving. He noted that with the teeming youth that Nigeria has and their great potentials, the country could attain greater heights in future. The Speaker also commended President Muhammadu Buhari for declaring November 1 of every year as Nigeria’s Youth Day.